div1.ab: In the District Court holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of William Spears and James M. McGough for a writ of Habeas Corpus |ss.
div1.p:
This same evening in for hearing on the ninth day of November 1883. upon the of the petitioners for their discharge The Court being duly advised in the premises, court rules said matter, and it is future ordered by this Court that the prosecuting be surrundered to allow before this Judge of said Court at Seattle on the seventeenth day of November 1883, at the time of the half past time of eleven in the afternoon. or an agreement mutually as from beforehand and that the eventual charge refueted to in the complaint is the procedural in issue the committment issued, under the respondent. A. G. Thomton claims to had said
petitons be them and there investigated.
div1.ab: June Application of Spears and Mc Gough for habeas corpus Filed Nov 9th 1883 James Seavey, Clerk. By James F. Ceass Deputy Clerk.
